In the not-too-distant future, after Earth has become a wasteland, man takes to the stars and begins colonizing other worlds under the direction of the Controllers, a cadre of smiling faces behind mirrored glasses that...well...control everything. When Officer Manhattan's first leader of the crew falls, the Controllers do not provide him with satisfactory answers as to why a robot was salvaged and Commander Falcon was not rescued. Then, when a mysterious robot called Addam Omega shows up as Falcon's replacement, Manhattan really has to wonder what the Controllers are up to. Space opera and intrigue from writer/artists Bill Hughes (Star Wars: Droids).

Thanks goes to Talon for this release.

